    "Mannerism in the 1930s was considered a deliberate distortion of the ideals of the Renaissance (and often compared to the Expressionism of Germany in their century).": [],
    "Schlosser himself had written on it.": [],
    "Gombrich asserted that the eccentricities of Giulio's Mannerist style, far from being degenerate, were employed for a patron eager for fashionable novelty.": [
