    "Gombrich's initial assignment at the Warburg Library in London was to ready Warburg's papers for publication.": [],
    "He astutely realized that Warburg's notes were not suitable for publication because of the juxtaposing way Warburg worked (see <em>DoAH</em> entry on Warburg) and Warburg's inability to draw lucid conclusions.": [],
    "Gombrich used his study of Warburg to write an intellectual biography of Warburg (1970, 2nd ed., 1985), which is by far the best introduction to Warburg's ideas.": []
